Production Handbook
Part 8 — Build Process, Quality Assurance & Production Rules

Document Type: Development Operations Manual

Status: Design Freeze Approved

Authority: This document governs how the website is implemented, reviewed, tested, deployed, and maintained. It establishes the production workflow and quality standards for the project.

Purpose

The purpose of this document is to ensure the website is built using a structured, repeatable process rather than an ad hoc development approach.

The implementation team shall:

Follow a consistent workflow
Verify quality continuously
Avoid unnecessary rework
Protect performance
Preserve the approved design
Maintain code quality
Development Philosophy

The website should be developed as if it will be maintained for many years.

Priorities:

Stability
Readability
Maintainability
Performance
Accessibility
Scalability

Code should always favor clarity over cleverness.

Production Workflow

Development shall proceed in the following order.

Phase 1

Project Initialization

Tasks

Create repository

Create folder structure

Configure development environment

Import assets

Verify design system

Phase 2

Foundation

Tasks

Build HTML structure

Configure CSS architecture

Implement typography

Create layout system

Configure variables

No JavaScript at this stage.

Phase 3

Core Components

Build:

Header

Navigation

Buttons

Cards

Forms

Footer

Trust Bar

Section headers

These become the reusable foundation for every page.

Phase 4

Homepage

Build homepage first.

Implement sections in approved order.

Do not begin secondary pages until homepage structure is complete.

Phase 5

Service Pages

Build reusable service template.

Populate:

Decks

Remodeling

Painting

Electrical

Handyman

Woodworking

Woodpecker Repair

Maintain identical structure across services.

Phase 6

Supporting Pages

Gallery

About

Reviews

Contact

Privacy Policy

404

Phase 7

Interactive Features

Implement:

Before/After Slider

Gallery filtering

Lightbox

FAQ accordion

Navigation animation

Form validation

Progressive enhancement should be used wherever possible.

Phase 8

SEO Implementation

Configure:

Metadata

Schema

Robots

Sitemap

Open Graph

Canonical URLs

Structured headings

Internal links

Phase 9

Optimization

Compress assets

Optimize CSS

Optimize JavaScript

Optimize images

Review Core Web Vitals

Run Lighthouse

Phase 10

Final QA

Accessibility

Responsive review

Browser testing

Performance review

Broken links

Forms

Launch checklist

Coding Standards

Every file should be:

Readable

Consistent

Modular

Commented where necessary

No dead code

No unused assets

No duplicate functionality

HTML Standards

Requirements

Semantic HTML

One H1 per page

Logical heading hierarchy

Accessible forms

Descriptive buttons

No inline styling

No presentational markup

CSS Standards

Requirements

Reusable classes

Component-based organization

No duplicated selectors

Consistent spacing

Logical naming

Avoid excessive specificity.

JavaScript Standards

JavaScript should enhance the experience—not create dependencies.

Requirements

Modular

Reusable

Graceful degradation

Error handling

Minimal global scope

Avoid blocking rendering.

Version Control

Every meaningful feature should be committed independently.

Examples

feat: create responsive navigation

feat: implement gallery component

fix: improve form accessibility

perf: optimize hero image loading

Commit frequently with descriptive messages.

Code Review Standards

Every completed feature should be reviewed for:

Readability
Accessibility
Performance
Browser compatibility
Consistency with design system
Mobile behavior

No feature should move forward without review.

Testing Strategy

Every page should be tested for:

Functionality

Visual consistency

Accessibility

Performance

SEO

Responsive behavior

Cross-browser compatibility

Responsive Testing

Minimum widths

320px

375px

390px

414px

768px

1024px

1280px

1440px

1920px

Verify:

Navigation

Forms

Gallery

Typography

Buttons

Spacing

No horizontal scrolling.

Browser Testing

Required

Chrome

Edge

Firefox

Safari

Mobile Chrome

Mobile Safari

Graceful degradation is acceptable for non-critical visual enhancements.

Accessibility Testing

Verify

Keyboard navigation

Focus order

Focus visibility

Screen reader compatibility

Color contrast

Touch targets

Form labels

ARIA usage where appropriate

No inaccessible interactions.

Performance Testing

Measure

Core Web Vitals

Image loading

JavaScript execution

CSS size

Font loading

Animation performance

Network requests

Optimize before launch.

Lighthouse Requirements

Minimum acceptable scores

Performance

95+

Accessibility

95+

Best Practices

95+

SEO

95+

These are launch requirements, not stretch goals.

Forms Testing

Verify

Validation

Submission

Confirmation

Spam protection

Mobile usability

Keyboard navigation

Required fields

No form should reach production untested.

Link Validation

Verify

Navigation links

Footer links

Buttons

Service links

Gallery links

Contact links

External links

No broken links permitted.

Image Validation

Verify

Responsive sizes

Compression

Alt text

Captions

Lazy loading

No distorted images.

Placeholder Verification

Before launch verify

Every placeholder documented

Placeholder images identified

Placeholder reviews removed or clearly approved

Owner portrait updated if available

No accidental placeholder content remains.

Deployment Process

Before deployment

Run final QA

Verify analytics

Verify forms

Verify Search Console

Generate sitemap

Generate robots.txt

Verify favicon

Confirm legal pages

Confirm contact information

Only then deploy.

Rollback Strategy

If critical issues are discovered after deployment

Restore previous version

Document issue

Resolve locally

Re-test

Redeploy

Never hotfix directly on production.

Post-Launch Monitoring

Monitor

404 errors

Core Web Vitals

Search Console

Analytics

Quote requests

Phone clicks

Form failures

Review these metrics regularly during the first 30 days.

Maintenance Schedule

Monthly

Review broken links

Update plugins (if applicable)

Review analytics

Optimize images

Check forms

Quarterly

Review SEO

Refresh project gallery

Add new reviews

Evaluate performance

Annually

Review design consistency

Review content accuracy

Review legal pages

Evaluate future improvements

Build Rules

The implementation team must not:

Change the navigation
Rewrite approved messaging
Modify the design system
Introduce new page layouts
Replace approved components
Remove trust elements
Change the CTA wording
Add unapproved animations
Introduce unnecessary libraries
Ignore accessibility requirements

If a change appears necessary, it must be documented and approved before implementation.

Production Freeze

The following are frozen:

Site architecture
Navigation
Design system
Component library
SEO strategy
Technical architecture
Asset structure
Messaging
Conversion strategy

The implementation phase is not a redesign phase.

Production Success Criteria

The website is considered complete only when:

Every approved page has been built
Every component matches the approved design system
All interactive features function correctly
Accessibility requirements are satisfied
Performance targets are achieved
SEO implementation is complete
QA checklist passes without critical issues
Client approval is obtained